t": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "I tend to do manually for now from time to time following errands manually for each (sub)dataset.  Primarily triggered by automated crawling, which can blow things up quite considerably ;)\r\n\r\n- dropping unused content, generally the one not pointed by a branch or a tag\r\n```\r\ngit annex unused --used-refspec +refs/heads/master:+refs/heads/incoming:+refs/tags/*\r\ngit annex dropunused all \r\n```\r\nso if may be would could specify some policy `datalad-cleanup-unused-refspec` so if specified, this step would be performed -- would be neat\r\n\r\n- git gc -- since we, to avoid side-effects from interaction of GitPython's in-memory view with our direct invocation of git commands, we disable gc while running git commands, we should run it manually from time to time.   So I just do\r\n\r\n```\r\ngit gc --prune=now \r\n```", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1371/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/datalad/datalad/issues/1371/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null}